            <h3> My Selection </h3>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Component</th>
                        <th>Image</th>
                        <th>Justification</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Adafruit 324</td>
                        <td><img src="media/Component_Selection/AdafruitMotor.bmp" alt="Adafruit Motor"
                                class="small-image"></td>
                        <td>Component familiarity combined with access to years of online discussion makes this the
                            superior choice. Already owning the part helps as well, as it negates the price downside. The
                            keyed axle makes mounting it to the 3d printed components a breeze. The only comparable option
                            would be the ROB-09238, but familiarity has immense value to me, especially given the complexity
                            of the motor driver selected. I would rather the motor itself be the easiest part to integrate.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
